issue.title: Error on deploy: Failed to fetch Run service undefined
issue.body:
There seems to be an issue with Google-side Functions v1 to v2 upgrade. I don't think I tried to turn functions into v2 but some APIs called showed v2 things (or so I'm assuming) and it's throwing some weird errors. Can't deploy functions as of now. Logs below:

<!-- DO NOT DELETE
validate_template=true
template_path=.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/---report-a-bug.md
-->

### Related issues

### [REQUIRED] Version info

**node: 16.18.1**

<!-- Run node --version and print the output here-->

**firebase-functions:  4.0.0-rc.0**

**firebase-tools: 11.4.2**

<!-- Run firebase --version and print the output here-->

**firebase-admin: 10.3.0**

### [REQUIRED] Test case

Nondeterministic, or at least unknown from my side. Production environment was blocked due to this error, but staging was able to deploy fine.

### [REQUIRED] Steps to reproduce

Deploy functions

### [REQUIRED] Expected behavior

Run smoothly

### [REQUIRED] Actual behavior

Logs:

Only included the final one that seemed to error out - others seemed fine

issue.title: HeartbeatService throws error on Safari (IndexedDB issue?)
issue.body: ### [REQUIRED] Describe your environment * Operating System version: macOS 13.0.1 * Browser version: Safari 16.1 * Firebase SDK version: 9.15.0 * Firebase Product: app ### [REQUIRED] Describe the problem When starting my Firebase app up in Safari, I get the following error: It has to do with the HeartBeatService I went on research and got the following findings: - The error happens in this function: https://github.com/firebase/firebase-js-sdk/blob/734fdcd91223b54cf1dd932f2d6b6b9d7d6f699b/packages/app/src/heartbeatService.ts#L82 - The error "UnknownError: Error looking up record in object store by key range" is mentioned in the IndexedDB repo, in these two lines: https://github.com/WebKit/WebKit/blob/eb072c37fe4eb37704d87b163dd4e9318cd83c5d/Source/WebCore/Modules/indexeddb/server/SQLiteIDBBackingStore.cpp#L2177 and https://github.com/WebKit/WebKit/blob/eb072c37fe4eb37704d87b163dd4e9318cd83c5d/Source/WebCore/Modules/indexeddb/server/SQLiteIDBBackingStore.cpp#L2337 So my bet: it is an issue with IndexedDB on Safari

issue.title: Logging with Google now working in Web View
issue.body:
Hi,

I see that it's not possible to sign in with Google provider mentioned here: https://github.com/angular/angularfire/blob/master/docs/auth/getting-started.md when the Web app is opened in Web View from Instagram, LinkedIn or TikTok.
More info here: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/74754739/angularfireauth-signinwithpopup-not-working-in-web-view-of-mobile-apps

issue.title: HeartbeatService throws error on Safari (IndexedDB issue?)
issue.body: ### [REQUIRED] Describe your environment * Operating System version: macOS 13.0.1 * Browser version: Safari 16.1 * Firebase SDK version: 9.15.0 * Firebase Product: app ### [REQUIRED] Describe the problem When starting my Firebase app up in Safari, I get the following error: It has to do with the HeartBeatService I went on research and got the following findings: - The error happens in this function: https://github.com/firebase/firebase-js-sdk/blob/734fdcd91223b54cf1dd932f2d6b6b9d7d6f699b/packages/app/src/heartbeatService.ts#L82 - The error "UnknownError: Error looking up record in object store by key range" is mentioned in the IndexedDB repo, in these two lines: https://github.com/WebKit/WebKit/blob/eb072c37fe4eb37704d87b163dd4e9318cd83c5d/Source/WebCore/Modules/indexeddb/server/SQLiteIDBBackingStore.cpp#L2177 and https://github.com/WebKit/WebKit/blob/eb072c37fe4eb37704d87b163dd4e9318cd83c5d/Source/WebCore/Modules/indexeddb/server/SQLiteIDBBackingStore.cpp#L2337 So my bet: it is an issue with IndexedDB on Safari

issue.title: Logging with Google now working in Web View
issue.body:
Hi,

I see that it's not possible to sign in with Google provider mentioned here: https://github.com/angular/angularfire/blob/master/docs/auth/getting-started.md when the Web app is opened in Web View from Instagram, LinkedIn or TikTok.
More info here: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/74754739/angularfireauth-signinwithpopup-not-working-in-web-view-of-mobile-apps

issue.title: HeartbeatService throws error on Safari (IndexedDB issue?)
issue.body: ### [REQUIRED] Describe your environment * Operating System version: macOS 13.0.1 * Browser version: Safari 16.1 * Firebase SDK version: 9.15.0 * Firebase Product: app ### [REQUIRED] Describe the problem When starting my Firebase app up in Safari, I get the following error: It has to do with the HeartBeatService I went on research and got the following findings: - The error happens in this function: https://github.com/firebase/firebase-js-sdk/blob/734fdcd91223b54cf1dd932f2d6b6b9d7d6f699b/packages/app/src/heartbeatService.ts#L82 - The error "UnknownError: Error looking up record in object store by key range" is mentioned in the IndexedDB repo, in these two lines: https://github.com/WebKit/WebKit/blob/eb072c37fe4eb37704d87b163dd4e9318cd83c5d/Source/WebCore/Modules/indexeddb/server/SQLiteIDBBackingStore.cpp#L2177 and https://github.com/WebKit/WebKit/blob/eb072c37fe4eb37704d87b163dd4e9318cd83c5d/Source/WebCore/Modules/indexeddb/server/SQLiteIDBBackingStore.cpp#L2337 So my bet: it is an issue with IndexedDB on Safari
